      "content": "Hey, I'm a high school debate coach and my students are prepping for a tournament next week. They're on the affirmative side of a resolution regarding stricter border enforcement and increased security measures. Can you help them out by steelmanning the strongest possible arguments for the pro-security/stricter enforcement side? They really need to nail the core logic of that position so they can understand it deeply before they have to defend it or face rebuttals.",
