      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When the border is treated as permeable, it signals that immigration laws are optional, which fundamentally erodes the concept of a sovereign legal jurisdiction. This creates a systemic breakdown because if laws can be ignored at the border, they become meaningless everywhere else. Economically, uncontrolled migration places an unsustainable burden on local infrastructure, schools, and social services, which are funded by taxpayers who did not consent to support that influx.",
      "source": "target",
